<h1>1.Creating new root branches</h1>


To do this move your mouse pointer over the file menu and click the left mouse button.

<br>

Then from the menu click on 'New root branch'.

<br>

You will be asked to provide a name for the branch / topic.


<h1>2. Creating new sub branch</h1>


To create a new sub branch move your mouse pointer over the branch.

<br>

Then press your right mouse button and select 'Add Sub branch'.

<br>

Then you will be asked for a name for the branch / topic.


<h1>3. Renaming a branch</h1>


To rename a branch move your mouse pointer over the branch.

<br>

Then press your right mouse button and select 'Rename branch'.


<h1>4. Deleting a branch</h1>


To delete a branch move your mouse pointer over the branch.

<br>

Then press your right mouse button and select 'Delete branch'.


<h1>5. Creating a branch link</h1>
As a means of avoiding repetition it is sometime useful to have the same topic shown under different branches.<BR>
To link to a branch drag (left click and move) your mouse pointer to where you would like the link to appear.<BR>
Then release your left mouse button.<BR>
A menu will appear, select 'Link branch here' and left click on it.<BR>
<br>
<h1>6. Changing branch icon</h1>

To change a branch icon move your mouse pointer over the branch.

<br>

Then press your right mouse button and select 'Properties', and select the 'Icons' tab.

<br>

You will now see a selection of icons, click on one and click OK.
<BR><BR>
<font color="#0000ff">
For more information please <a href="<% = lstrPGBranchprops %>#Branch_icons">click here</a>.
</font>
<br>
<h1>7. Changing branch sorting</h1>

By default, branches are sorted alphabetically. &nbsp;You can specify numbered ordering too.

<br>

On the menu select 'Tools' then 'Options'. &nbsp;Then select the 'Sort Order' tab, and choose 'Branch sequence number'.

<br>

Then to specify sequence number for a branch, move your mouse pointer over a branch and press your right mouse button, then select 'Properties'.

<br>

Change the sequence number to a higher number to move the branch down the tree.

<br>

NB. Zero if the lowest number.

<BR><BR>
<font color="#0000ff">
For more information please <a href="<% = lstrPGBranchprops %>">click here</a>.
</font>

<h1>8. Printing / Saving Rich Text</h1>

You can print the current topic by clicking on the print button on the toolbar.

<br>

OR
<br>
Use the 'Selective Print' feature from the file menu.
<BR>
OR
<BR>
Use the 'Export' feature to save as a 'Rich Text File (RTF)'.

<br><br>
<font color="#0000ff">
Here you can select certain topics and then print or export them (save them to an RTF document).
</font>

<h1>9. Using a Template</h1>

Select the 'Templates menu' then click on the 'Select Template' Option.<BR>
A 'Template Selection' screen will be shown.  On the left are all the standard templates.<BR>
Select one 'Address Form' for example, now click the 'Select' button.<BR>
On the next screen select 'Create a new root topic' and click the 'OK' button.<BR>
You will be prompted to provide a name for your topic, similar to above (creating branches).<BR>
<br>
<font color="#0000ff">
For more information please <a href="<% = lstrPGTemplatesProvided %>">click here</a>.
</font>

